claim: Bats have lost their webbed wings.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Bats are mammals of the order Chiroptera  (  -LSB- kaɪˈrɒptərə -RSB- from the χείρ - cheir , `` hand '' and πτερόν - pteron , `` wing ''  )  whose forelimbs form webbed wings , making them the only mammals naturally capable of true and sustained flight .
